{"info": {"author": "Praekelt Foundation", "author_email": "dev@praekeltfoundation.org", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: Developers", "Natural Language :: English", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7"], "description": "heatherrd\n=============================\n\n.. image:: https://img.shields.io/travis/smn/heatherrd.svg\n        :target: https://travis-ci.org/smn/heatherrd\n\n.. image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/heatherrd.svg\n        :target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/heatherrd\n\n.. image:: https://coveralls.io/repos/smn/heatherrd/badge.png?branch=develop\n    :target: https://coveralls.io/r/smn/heatherrd?branch=develop\n    :alt: Code Coverage\n\nA simple Python microservice that turns RTM into a synchronous HTTP interface.\n\n::\n\n    $ pip install heatherrd\n    $ heatherrd --listen=tcp:8001 --url=http://example.com/callback-url/\n\n::\n\n    $ curl --user <bot-user-id>:<bot-access-token> http://localhost:8001/connect\n\nI'll maintain the RTM connections for the bot and relay incoming RTM messages\nas JSON to the URL provided.\n\nThe URL can echo a list of RTM responses as JSON which will be sent back\nover the RTM connection as a reply.", "description_content_type": null, "docs_url": "https://pythonhosted.org/heatherrd/", "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/smn/heatherrd", "keywords": "heatherrd", "license": "BSD", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "heatherrd", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/heatherrd/", "platform": "UNKNOWN", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/heatherrd/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/smn/heatherrd"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/heatherrd/1.0.0/", "requires_dist": ["Klein (==15.3.1)", "click (==6.2)", "treq (==15.1.0)", "autobahn (==0.12.1)"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "This is the heatherrd project.", "version": "1.0.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/smn/heatherrd\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"https://img.shields.io/travis/smn/heatherrd.svg\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/8aa54b9a2c838a66871e19f2e0f790471bf61c5a/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f7472617669732f736d6e2f6865617468657272642e737667\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://pypi.python.org/pypi/heatherrd\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/heatherrd.svg\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/d7538cb92c5ed81fb8aa1c3eb2e6f33f43495217/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f707970692f762f6865617468657272642e737667\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://coveralls.io/r/smn/heatherrd?branch=develop\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Code Coverage\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/f314405f0814554196125471af4a571a2243edad/68747470733a2f2f636f766572616c6c732e696f2f7265706f732f736d6e2f6865617468657272642f62616467652e706e673f6272616e63683d646576656c6f70\"></a>\n<p>A simple Python microservice that turns RTM into a synchronous HTTP interface.</p>\n<pre>$ pip install heatherrd\n$ heatherrd --listen=tcp:8001 --url=http://example.com/callback-url/\n</pre>\n<pre>$ curl --user &lt;bot-user-id&gt;:&lt;bot-access-token&gt; http://localhost:8001/connect\n</pre>\n<p>I\u2019ll maintain the RTM connections for the bot and relay incoming RTM messages\nas JSON to the URL provided.</p>\n<p>The URL can echo a list of RTM responses as JSON which will be sent back\nover the RTM connection as a reply.</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 1952960, "releases": {"0.1.0": [], "1.0.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "47b211eb6902b3b13ae08339974b67b5", "sha256": "46c2c9965ef8aa786644ac071a932cc80df0910e792e790201e316649ae920ce"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "heatherrd-1.0.0-py2-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "47b211eb6902b3b13ae08339974b67b5", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version":